1
00:00:22,464 --> 00:00:26,432
♪Should we forget yesterday's sorrows♪

2
00:00:26,432 --> 00:00:29,728
♪And the dazed confusion♪

3
00:00:30,976 --> 00:00:33,681
♪Should we let go of♪

4
00:00:33,681 --> 00:00:35,904
♪The stubborn madness♪

5
00:00:35,904 --> 00:00:39,072
♪And naive recklessness now♪

6
00:00:40,192 --> 00:00:43,840
♪Those years, those faces♪

7
00:00:44,992 --> 00:00:48,763
♪Those old scars we can't erase♪

8
00:00:49,824 --> 00:00:52,460
♪Tears streaming, facing the light♪

9
00:00:53,152 --> 00:00:57,594
♪Piercing the sorrow within♪

10
00:01:08,716 --> 00:01:12,736
♪The road ahead's long,
stumbling all the way♪

11
00:01:13,536 --> 00:01:18,076
♪The wounds we've borne
are medals hidden within♪

12
00:01:18,336 --> 00:01:22,391
♪Standing alone on an open plain♪

13
00:01:23,168 --> 00:01:26,851
♪We gaze at the stars♪

14
00:01:31,228 --> 00:01:34,816
=The Dream Maker=

15
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,912
=Episode 38=

16
00:01:39,552 --> 00:01:40,052
Exactly.

17
00:01:41,440 --> 00:01:42,201
I'm just scared.

18
00:01:43,761 --> 00:01:45,961
I'm worried I can't do it.

19
00:01:46,360 --> 00:01:47,601
150 million.

20
00:01:48,201 --> 00:01:48,720
Mr. Zheng,

21
00:01:49,961 --> 00:01:51,640
you want me to manage 150 million?

22
00:01:51,921 --> 00:01:53,201
That's not the issue right now.

23
00:01:55,841 --> 00:01:57,304
You know I take things seriously.

24
00:01:58,201 --> 00:01:59,280
Lately,

25
00:01:59,321 --> 00:02:01,681
I haven't been sleeping well.

26
00:02:01,720 --> 00:02:02,840
I'm telling you,

27
00:02:04,121 --> 00:02:04,720
there is

28
00:02:05,720 --> 00:02:07,160
a sharp pain in my chest and ribs.

29
00:02:07,201 --> 00:02:08,921
My mind has been racing.

30
00:02:09,041 --> 00:02:11,080
It's probably just from lack of sleep.

31
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:14,520
Even if I can manage it this time,

32
00:02:15,321 --> 00:02:16,024
the point is

33
00:02:16,161 --> 00:02:17,840
that Yuehai is developing too fast.

34
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:20,201
I feel my abilities aren't enough.

35
00:02:20,520 --> 00:02:22,400
Today, it's 150 million,
what about tomorrow?

36
00:02:22,560 --> 00:02:23,640
If I did it today,

37
00:02:23,640 --> 00:02:25,272
I'd have to manage 15 billion tomorrow.

38
00:02:25,272 --> 00:02:26,360
How do I manage that?

39
00:02:26,881 --> 00:02:28,504
Currently, Yuehai is growing

40
00:02:28,504 --> 00:02:29,848
as fast as the rockets

41
00:02:29,848 --> 00:02:31,512
blasting off into space.

42
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:33,640
It shoots straight up into the sky.

43
00:02:35,640 --> 00:02:36,824
It flies so fast.

44
00:02:38,680 --> 00:02:40,001
It's like a rocket.

45
00:02:40,041 --> 00:02:41,528
It's made up of stages, right?

46
00:02:41,848 --> 00:02:43,192
So, it's built in stages.

47
00:02:43,640 --> 00:02:46,400
When the rocket pushes
through the atmosphere

48
00:02:46,481 --> 00:02:47,416
and breaks out,

49
00:02:47,601 --> 00:02:49,560
it has a booster, the first part.

50
00:02:50,041 --> 00:02:52,321
Once it completes its mission,

51
00:02:52,360 --> 00:02:53,496
it gets jettisoned.

52
00:02:54,161 --> 00:02:54,960
It becomes useless.

53
00:02:57,761 --> 00:02:58,881
I'm done.

54
00:03:09,640 --> 00:03:10,441
What do you mean?

55
00:03:12,601 --> 00:03:14,120
Are you abandoning us?

56
00:03:15,041 --> 00:03:16,536
You said you didn't sleep well.

57
00:03:17,848 --> 00:03:19,576
Since I arrived in Yuehai,

58
00:03:19,680 --> 00:03:21,640
I haven't slept well for a single night.

59
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:22,488
Do you know that?

60
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:25,721
I'm scared too.

61
00:03:27,321 --> 00:03:28,088
You think I'm not?

62
00:03:29,441 --> 00:03:30,936
But what I fear isn't lack of money.

63
00:03:31,161 --> 00:03:32,216
You know what my fear is?

64
00:03:33,321 --> 00:03:35,576
I fear Yuehai will stop developing.

65
00:03:35,761 --> 00:03:37,784
I fear it will stagnate under our watch.

66
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:40,568
Sometimes,

67
00:03:41,240 --> 00:03:41,816
it's not

68
00:03:43,161 --> 00:03:44,600
that we choose our destiny,

69
00:03:46,161 --> 00:03:48,001
but that destiny chooses us.

70
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:51,480
We were chosen by destiny.

71
00:03:51,480 --> 00:03:53,144
We were chosen by this era.

72
00:03:53,721 --> 00:03:55,672
Now Yuehai is entrusted to us.

73
00:03:55,921 --> 00:03:58,761
We are responsible for its future.

74
00:04:00,281 --> 00:04:02,041
Yuehai is like our child.

75
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:05,112
We've watched it grow, bit by bit,

76
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:08,840
from day one to now.

77
00:04:09,001 --> 00:04:10,104
It's a big child now.

78
00:04:10,104 --> 00:04:11,640
How could you abandon it now?

79
00:04:13,001 --> 00:04:15,544
It's weird, but I can actually
picture it all in my head.

80
00:04:15,544 --> 00:04:16,921
I always see a picture.

81
00:04:17,081 --> 00:04:17,688
What is it?

82
00:04:18,320 --> 00:04:19,864
When we're old,

83
00:04:21,281 --> 00:04:22,520
we come back.

84
00:04:22,841 --> 00:04:23,960
We support each other,

85
00:04:24,440 --> 00:04:26,161
standing by Yuehai.

86
00:04:26,680 --> 00:04:27,560
There's a stone.

87
00:04:28,281 --> 00:04:29,496
On it is carved the names

88
00:04:30,081 --> 00:04:31,721
of a few old men.

89
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,000
Zheng Decheng.

90
00:04:35,281 --> 00:04:36,320
Tan Guangming.

91
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:39,128
My name is right next to yours.

92
00:04:39,601 --> 00:04:40,440
Do you understand?

93
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:42,552
We are next to each other.

94
00:04:43,961 --> 00:04:45,401
On the memorial stone,

95
00:04:46,721 --> 00:04:48,481
your name can't be missing.

96
00:04:49,041 --> 00:04:51,760
We must be together, Tan.

97
00:04:58,200 --> 00:04:59,224
I'll do it.

98
00:04:59,224 --> 00:05:00,056
You sit down.

99
00:05:15,880 --> 00:05:16,664
Mr. Zheng.

100
00:05:19,041 --> 00:05:20,952
I'm sorry.
I never wanted my name remembered.

101
00:05:21,161 --> 00:05:23,000
Tan, I know you.

102
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:26,232
I owe you an apology.

103
00:05:27,760 --> 00:05:30,000
Who is the Secretary of Yuehai?

104
00:05:30,760 --> 00:05:31,320
Me.

105
00:05:31,921 --> 00:05:32,601
Zheng Decheng.

106
00:05:33,161 --> 00:05:35,641
If the sky falls, I'll hold it up!

107
00:05:36,240 --> 00:05:36,740
Alright?

108
00:05:37,401 --> 00:05:40,088
I just need you to help me.

109
00:05:40,760 --> 00:05:41,260
Okay?

110
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:43,961
Just help me.

111
00:05:44,521 --> 00:05:45,021
Please.

112
00:05:48,385 --> 00:05:51,708
♪The white doves across the lake♪

113
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:54,300
Come on.

114
00:05:56,721 --> 00:05:57,221
Sit.

115
00:05:58,200 --> 00:06:01,204
♪Your persistence♪

116
00:06:01,841 --> 00:06:03,192
You really need me?

117
00:06:04,521 --> 00:06:06,008
Of course!

118
00:06:06,008 --> 00:06:09,944
♪You're the wind-stirred river
of my heart♪

119
00:06:10,041 --> 00:06:12,200
Then, you must promise me one thing.

120
00:06:12,601 --> 00:06:13,101
Go ahead.

121
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:15,032
You must find someone in the future,

122
00:06:15,032 --> 00:06:16,560
whose abilities surpass mine,

123
00:06:17,120 --> 00:06:18,648
to take over my position.

124
00:06:18,721 --> 00:06:19,640
You can't let me

125
00:06:19,640 --> 00:06:21,440
hold back Yuehai's development
in this role.

126
00:06:22,456 --> 00:06:26,862
♪Your silhouette
still lingers before my eyes♪

127
00:06:28,320 --> 00:06:29,120
I'm so happy

128
00:06:30,161 --> 00:06:32,152
to have known you in my life.

129
00:06:34,760 --> 00:06:36,120
We're good friends for life.

130
00:06:40,216 --> 00:06:44,240
♪You're the gentle passage of a book♪

131
00:06:44,543 --> 00:06:48,856
♪Sweeping me away like a gust of wind♪

132
00:06:51,401 --> 00:06:53,688
Today's class assignment is too hard.

133
00:06:53,688 --> 00:06:56,600
- Don't worry. Review it later.
- I can't memorize the commands.

134
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:58,560
We won't use

135
00:06:58,641 --> 00:06:59,800
the disk operating system.

136
00:07:00,440 --> 00:07:01,144
What will we use?

137
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:02,840
Now, we use Microsoft's Windows.

138
00:07:03,281 --> 00:07:06,281
The Windows is user-friendly and quick.

139
00:07:06,360 --> 00:07:07,992
- I don't know about Windows.
- You know what?

140
00:07:08,481 --> 00:07:09,368
The Windows...

141
00:07:09,368 --> 00:07:11,416
Could there have been an ancient tomb?

142
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:13,368
Maybe it drifted here from the sea.

143
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:16,344
Do you think
there might be a shipwreck nearby?

144
00:07:16,344 --> 00:07:17,432
- Maybe.
- It's possible.

145
00:07:17,432 --> 00:07:18,648
That would be incredible.

146
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:21,081
Back then, Eunuch Sanbao

147
00:07:21,081 --> 00:07:23,928
brought back plenty of treasures
on his voyages to the Western Seas.

148
00:07:24,120 --> 00:07:25,200
Unfortunately,

149
00:07:25,200 --> 00:07:26,744
an order was issued,

150
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:28,280
banning sea voyages.

151
00:07:29,041 --> 00:07:31,081
Many treasures were lost.

152
00:07:31,841 --> 00:07:33,521
Do you think that ship

153
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:34,760
might have sunk in Yuehai?

154
00:07:34,760 --> 00:07:35,672
Very possible.

155
00:07:36,280 --> 00:07:37,496
- Don't push!
- Stop pushing!

156
00:07:37,496 --> 00:07:39,352
Protect the scene! Don't touch anything!

157
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:40,344
Come on.

158
00:07:40,440 --> 00:07:41,760
- Make way!
- Folks!

159
00:07:41,760 --> 00:07:43,576
- Step aside!
- Step aside!

160
00:07:43,576 --> 00:07:45,112
We need to protect the scene!

161
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:46,840
Yes, step aside!

162
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:52,536
(City Inspector)

163
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:54,401
Listen,

164
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:56,981
whoever found this, please stay behind.

165
00:07:57,200 --> 00:08:00,120
Everyone else, please head home for now.

166
00:08:00,120 --> 00:08:00,721
Don't stay.

167
00:08:00,760 --> 00:08:02,424
We don't want the scene disturbed, okay?

168
00:08:02,760 --> 00:08:03,601
Mr. Tan,

169
00:08:03,601 --> 00:08:05,401
if there are treasures in this sea,

170
00:08:05,401 --> 00:08:06,760
(City Inspector)
we should stop the project.

171
00:08:06,760 --> 00:08:08,601
Otherwise,
the treasures would be buried.

172
00:08:09,081 --> 00:08:11,000
Mr. Tan, stop the project!

173
00:08:11,521 --> 00:08:12,728
We can't demolish this!

174
00:08:12,728 --> 00:08:13,320
(City Inspector)

175
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:14,040
Guys.

176
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:15,620
- Don't you agree?
- Yeah!

177
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:16,440
Can't demolish it!

178
00:08:16,601 --> 00:08:18,008
Stop the project!

179
00:08:18,552 --> 00:08:25,552
(Commendation Banners)

180
00:08:34,361 --> 00:08:34,921
Mr. Tang,

181
00:08:35,121 --> 00:08:36,480
are these all antiques?

182
00:08:37,921 --> 00:08:39,800
A few genuinely are old items.

183
00:08:40,281 --> 00:08:42,104
The first item is
from the late Qianlong era.

184
00:08:43,041 --> 00:08:44,161
The second bowl is likely

185
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:47,032
from the Jiaqing or Daoguang reign.

186
00:08:47,121 --> 00:08:49,560
The rest are
from the Republic of China period,

187
00:08:49,680 --> 00:08:50,936
not really antiques.

188
00:08:52,521 --> 00:08:55,128
Two of them are even younger than me.

189
00:08:56,921 --> 00:08:57,881
Could they possibly

190
00:08:57,881 --> 00:08:59,896
be burial objects from a tomb?

191
00:09:00,041 --> 00:09:00,720
Impossible.

192
00:09:02,161 --> 00:09:04,960
The eras of the artifacts don't match,
and the styles differ.

193
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:06,456
They can't be funerary objects.

194
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:09,241
Then, could they be from a shipwreck?

195
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:10,200
Even less likely.

196
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:11,736
Sea-salvaged porcelain

197
00:09:12,320 --> 00:09:14,872
should show signs of seawater corrosion.

198
00:09:15,281 --> 00:09:17,496
Yet none of them show signs
of seawater immersion.

199
00:09:18,720 --> 00:09:19,960
The 'monkeys' on Binhai Road

200
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:21,560
must have buried them.

201
00:09:21,881 --> 00:09:23,704
I can't tell exactly who buried them.

202
00:09:24,241 --> 00:09:24,800
Alright.

203
00:09:25,241 --> 00:09:26,808
I've looked at the items. I'm leaving.

204
00:09:27,001 --> 00:09:28,521
Thank you. Let me see you out.

205
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:33,300
Mr. Tang.

206
00:09:33,560 --> 00:09:34,776
Could you provide us

207
00:09:34,776 --> 00:09:36,200
with an appraisal certificate?

208
00:09:36,241 --> 00:09:37,336
Yes, no problem.

209
00:09:37,440 --> 00:09:38,121
Goodbye then.

210
00:09:38,281 --> 00:09:39,352
Okay, take care.

211
00:09:41,041 --> 00:09:42,161
I'll find those 'monkeys'.

212
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:45,368
I'll find the one
who buried those 'antiques'.

213
00:09:46,401 --> 00:09:47,992
Mr. Zheng, don't worry.

214
00:09:48,241 --> 00:09:49,720
Who buried them isn't important.

215
00:09:50,600 --> 00:09:51,440
Then, what matters?

216
00:09:52,560 --> 00:09:53,440
It's Binhai Road.

217
00:09:54,241 --> 00:09:56,440
What I care about most
is Gao Xuemei's attitude.

218
00:10:02,480 --> 00:10:05,848
Actually, I want to support this matter.

219
00:10:06,616 --> 00:10:07,361
But...

220
00:10:08,001 --> 00:10:08,680
I understand.

221
00:10:09,241 --> 00:10:11,736
Binhai Road is crucial
for many businesses,

222
00:10:11,921 --> 00:10:14,440
because they're based
only on Binhai Road.

223
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:15,768
But you're different.

224
00:10:16,281 --> 00:10:18,840
Chunmei Printery has long been expanded.

225
00:10:19,041 --> 00:10:20,521
The brand is already established.

226
00:10:20,881 --> 00:10:23,160
Binhai Road is nonessential for you.

227
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:25,080
If you only consider your own interests,

228
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:26,800
you'd definitely sign.

229
00:10:27,641 --> 00:10:29,880
But now, you're the head
of the Printing Association.

230
00:10:30,041 --> 00:10:31,576
Your decision is critical.

231
00:10:32,641 --> 00:10:34,104
So what you must consider isn't

232
00:10:34,104 --> 00:10:35,521
your personal gains and losses,

233
00:10:35,921 --> 00:10:38,521
but the collective interests
of those self-employed individuals.

234
00:10:38,840 --> 00:10:39,704
Ms. Li.

235
00:10:40,001 --> 00:10:41,401
You already know all this.

236
00:10:41,521 --> 00:10:42,840
Why did you still call me here?

237
00:10:44,361 --> 00:10:45,761
I'm curious about one thing.

238
00:10:46,121 --> 00:10:49,361
After weighing the pros and cons,
what will you do?

239
00:10:50,161 --> 00:10:51,320
What I think isn't important.

240
00:10:51,641 --> 00:10:53,592
What matters is
those hundred-plus businesses.

241
00:10:53,960 --> 00:10:56,120
They all have the right
to make their own choices.

242
00:10:56,361 --> 00:10:58,800
And I must respect their decisions.

243
00:10:59,161 --> 00:11:00,320
But I still want to know.

244
00:11:00,840 --> 00:11:02,488
If you had the power to decide,

245
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:04,216
would you sign or not?

246
00:11:08,560 --> 00:11:11,128
I've carefully reviewed your notice.

247
00:11:11,401 --> 00:11:12,696
In the best-case scenario,

248
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:15,064
the land could be delivered
in five years.

249
00:11:16,281 --> 00:11:17,560
But five years from now,

250
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:19,992
where will you and Mr. Zheng be?

251
00:11:20,560 --> 00:11:22,264
If you both leave Yuehai,

252
00:11:22,560 --> 00:11:24,440
who can guarantee
none of this will change?

253
00:11:27,840 --> 00:11:29,521
Protect Yuehai's treasure.

254
00:11:29,521 --> 00:11:31,160
- Protect Yuehai's treasure!
- Protect Yuehai's treasure!

255
00:11:31,160 --> 00:11:32,664
We want seafood, not cement.

256
00:11:32,888 --> 00:11:34,616
- We want seafood, not cement!
- We want seafood, not cement!

257
00:11:34,616 --> 00:11:35,832
Protect Yuehai's treasure!

258
00:11:36,521 --> 00:11:38,360
- Protect Yuehai's treasure!
- Protect Yuehai's treasure!

259
00:11:38,360 --> 00:11:40,761
- We want seafood, not cement!
- We want seafood, not cement!

260
00:11:40,761 --> 00:11:42,296
Protect Yuehai's treasure!

261
00:11:42,401 --> 00:11:43,921
(We Want Seafood, Not Cement)
Protect Yuehai's treasure!

262
00:11:43,960 --> 00:11:44,728
Wait, you all...

263
00:11:44,921 --> 00:11:46,936
- What are you doing?
- Protect Yuehai's treasure!

264
00:11:46,936 --> 00:11:48,680
- Protect Yuehai's treasure!
- Protect Yuehai's treasure!

265
00:11:48,680 --> 00:11:50,424
Protect Yuehai's treasure!

266
00:11:50,424 --> 00:11:52,184
- Protect Yuehai's treasure!
- Protect Yuehai's treasure!

267
00:11:53,784 --> 00:11:56,320
- We want seafood, not cement!
- Don't fight!

268
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:58,041
- We want seafood, not cement!
- Listen to Mr. Tan!

269
00:11:58,041 --> 00:12:00,344
Right, we can talk
about whatever issues we have.

270
00:12:00,344 --> 00:12:01,752
- Right?
- Yes.

271
00:12:01,921 --> 00:12:06,776
Currently, Xuemei is negotiating
the relocation agreement.

272
00:12:07,032 --> 00:12:07,928
Let's wait for news.

273
00:12:08,161 --> 00:12:10,241
(City Inspector)
Before she finishes,

274
00:12:10,241 --> 00:12:11,640
I suggest we find a tent.

275
00:12:12,161 --> 00:12:14,541
- Smoke a cigarette and have some tea.
- Good.

276
00:12:14,680 --> 00:12:16,281
You do your thing.
We'll keep doing this.

277
00:12:16,320 --> 00:12:17,480
Protect Yuehai's treasure!

278
00:12:17,480 --> 00:12:19,121
- Protect Yuehai's treasure!
- Protect Yuehai's treasure!

279
00:12:19,121 --> 00:12:20,568
Protect Yuehai's treasure!

280
00:12:20,568 --> 00:12:22,104
- Protect Yuehai's treasure!
- Protect Yuehai's treasure!

281
00:12:22,162 --> 00:12:23,832
- We want seafood, not cement!
- Lin.

282
00:12:24,320 --> 00:12:24,881
Mr. Qi.

283
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:26,041
(City Inspector)
Right now,

284
00:12:26,480 --> 00:12:28,161
just take a break, alright?

285
00:12:28,241 --> 00:12:29,880
The situation is uncontrollable.

286
00:12:30,001 --> 00:12:31,320
You shouldn't be stopping us.

287
00:12:31,401 --> 00:12:32,761
You should arrest them all.

288
00:12:32,761 --> 00:12:33,680
Arrest who?

289
00:12:33,784 --> 00:12:34,360
Who?

290
00:12:34,881 --> 00:12:35,381
Hear it?

291
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:36,472
He wants to arrest us!

292
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:37,400
- No!
- Why?

293
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:38,121
We can't...

294
00:12:38,121 --> 00:12:39,640
We can't arrest you.

295
00:12:39,960 --> 00:12:41,680
We're just city inspectors.

296
00:12:41,680 --> 00:12:42,936
We can't arrest you.

297
00:12:42,936 --> 00:12:44,600
- Calm down!
- What treasure?

298
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:47,320
I bet you're the ones who buried it.

299
00:12:48,440 --> 00:12:49,592
Baseless accusations!

300
00:12:50,161 --> 00:12:51,001
Our ancestors

301
00:12:51,384 --> 00:12:53,272
(City Inspector)
left this for us, right?

302
00:12:53,432 --> 00:12:54,600
- Yes!
- Yes!

303
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:55,864
I think you're a fake expert.

304
00:12:55,960 --> 00:12:56,888
Get out of Yuehai!

305
00:12:57,480 --> 00:12:58,361
Watch your tone!

306
00:12:58,584 --> 00:12:59,512
Mind your attitude.

307
00:12:59,832 --> 00:13:00,760
The mastermind!

308
00:13:01,680 --> 00:13:02,440
The mastermind!

309
00:13:03,041 --> 00:13:04,088
Say that again.

310
00:13:04,401 --> 00:13:05,432
What can you do?

311
00:13:05,641 --> 00:13:06,584
What can you do?

312
00:13:19,480 --> 00:13:20,152
My waist!

313
00:13:22,281 --> 00:13:22,872
Stop it!

314
00:13:23,096 --> 00:13:24,184
Stop fighting!

315
00:13:25,459 --> 00:13:27,248
Excuse me,
is the inpatient ward over there?

316
00:13:27,328 --> 00:13:28,027
Yes.

317
00:13:29,464 --> 00:13:31,161
(Next, a local news update.)

318
00:13:31,161 --> 00:13:32,600
Don't you think you've gone too far?

319
00:13:37,001 --> 00:13:38,488
You even called the TV station.

320
00:13:38,840 --> 00:13:41,368
Are you deliberately trying
to embarrass Mr. Zheng and Ms. Li?

321
00:13:42,521 --> 00:13:43,320
Listen,

322
00:13:44,480 --> 00:13:46,200
they really weren't called by me.

323
00:13:46,641 --> 00:13:47,832
They came on their own.

324
00:13:47,832 --> 00:13:48,632
They interviewed me.

325
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:50,220
- I couldn't refuse.
- Nurse.

326
00:13:50,440 --> 00:13:51,921
Is Qian Changyuan in this ward?

327
00:13:52,824 --> 00:13:53,816
Yes. Right inside.

328
00:13:53,816 --> 00:13:54,800
Are you crazy?

329
00:13:57,001 --> 00:13:57,501
Ms. Li.

330
00:13:58,800 --> 00:14:00,248
You don't have to buy many things.

331
00:14:00,248 --> 00:14:00,952
You're too kind.

332
00:14:05,521 --> 00:14:06,600
I have a concussion.

333
00:14:06,600 --> 00:14:07,800
I must have a concussion.

334
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:10,104
Aren't you overreacting?

335
00:14:13,560 --> 00:14:14,521
Thank you, Ms. Li.

336
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:16,056
Much better.

337
00:14:16,921 --> 00:14:17,560
Mr. Qi.

338
00:14:19,521 --> 00:14:20,440
I came here

339
00:14:20,440 --> 00:14:22,552
to bring Mr. Qi to apologize to you.

340
00:14:33,761 --> 00:14:34,600
To be honest,

341
00:14:34,680 --> 00:14:36,761
I don't think
you're right on this matter.

342
00:14:37,641 --> 00:14:39,320
But since you're both injured,

343
00:14:39,881 --> 00:14:41,401
I'll represent the survey team

344
00:14:41,521 --> 00:14:43,401
and offer you an apology.

345
00:14:50,840 --> 00:14:51,340
Look,

346
00:14:51,680 --> 00:14:52,761
what's that attitude?

347
00:14:52,761 --> 00:14:53,784
Enough now.

348
00:14:54,641 --> 00:14:55,241
Changyuan,

349
00:14:55,761 --> 00:14:57,304
sorry about this incident.

350
00:14:57,680 --> 00:14:59,160
But I've already told the hospital.

351
00:14:59,680 --> 00:15:01,400
All your treatment costs

352
00:15:01,480 --> 00:15:03,128
will be covered by the town government.

353
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:04,248
No need.

354
00:15:04,440 --> 00:15:05,624
Don't leave the hospital

355
00:15:05,720 --> 00:15:06,840
until you're fully healed.

356
00:15:08,320 --> 00:15:08,840
Ms. Li.

357
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:09,848
What about me?

358
00:15:10,440 --> 00:15:12,376
I have a concussion.

359
00:15:12,680 --> 00:15:13,784
Stop it.

360
00:15:14,241 --> 00:15:14,881
What?

361
00:15:15,521 --> 00:15:16,021
It hurts.

362
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:17,960
Let's step outside to talk.

363
00:15:20,680 --> 00:15:22,072
What are you doing? Shut up.

364
00:15:36,080 --> 00:15:36,641
Fatty.

365
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:40,056
You bought those antiques dug up
from the beach, didn't you?

366
00:15:40,320 --> 00:15:40,881
Ms. Li,

367
00:15:41,241 --> 00:15:42,161
that's baseless.

368
00:15:42,361 --> 00:15:43,256
Don't frame me.

369
00:15:43,800 --> 00:15:46,232
A junk dealer saw your TV interview.

370
00:15:46,521 --> 00:15:47,720
He's claimed

371
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:50,440
that you bought those antiques from him.

372
00:15:51,521 --> 00:15:52,320
I didn't.

373
00:15:52,680 --> 00:15:53,368
I don't know.

374
00:15:55,041 --> 00:15:56,184
What's going on here?

375
00:15:56,184 --> 00:15:57,200
Fatty, it's them.

376
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:58,100
Hey.

377
00:15:58,720 --> 00:15:59,448
Get out of here!

378
00:15:59,448 --> 00:16:00,504
This is my place.

379
00:16:00,680 --> 00:16:01,761
You're turning my place

380
00:16:01,761 --> 00:16:02,840
into an antique mall?

381
00:16:02,921 --> 00:16:05,080
Sir, I came from
the Nanzhou secondhand market.

382
00:16:05,080 --> 00:16:06,761
- I don't care.
- Genuine items.

383
00:16:06,761 --> 00:16:07,261
Leave!

384
00:16:07,361 --> 00:16:08,881
Who allowed you to be here?

385
00:16:08,881 --> 00:16:10,001
If you don't leave,

386
00:16:10,001 --> 00:16:11,641
my truck might crush your stuff.

387
00:16:11,720 --> 00:16:13,368
But I won't compensate you. Understand?

388
00:16:13,368 --> 00:16:14,521
- Fine, I'll leave.
- Yes.

389
00:16:14,521 --> 00:16:15,352
Get out of here!

390
00:16:15,600 --> 00:16:16,376
If he's still here,

391
00:16:16,376 --> 00:16:17,176
just call Tan.

392
00:16:27,560 --> 00:16:29,496
Those antiques are now
at the government office.

393
00:16:29,881 --> 00:16:31,128
After expert appraisal,

394
00:16:31,128 --> 00:16:33,432
some are genuine and quite valuable.

395
00:16:33,761 --> 00:16:35,161
Would you like to pick them up?

396
00:16:35,440 --> 00:16:36,881
Or should we send them to you?

397
00:16:37,960 --> 00:16:39,241
Ms. Li, you...

398
00:16:40,241 --> 00:16:42,840
You called me here just to say this?

399
00:16:44,521 --> 00:16:46,041
What else did you expect me to say?

400
00:16:49,480 --> 00:16:49,980
Fatty.

401
00:16:50,320 --> 00:16:52,600
I'm not here to hold you accountable.

402
00:16:52,881 --> 00:16:53,680
I also know

403
00:16:53,680 --> 00:16:55,680
you didn't do all this for yourself.

404
00:16:56,041 --> 00:16:58,840
You did it all for those
self-employed individuals

405
00:16:58,840 --> 00:17:01,200
on Binhai Road
who don't want to relocate,

406
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:01,700
right?

407
00:17:06,121 --> 00:17:07,000
No matter what,

408
00:17:07,081 --> 00:17:08,888
the situation has escalated
to this point.

409
00:17:09,081 --> 00:17:11,401
The town government
should be responsible.

410
00:17:11,680 --> 00:17:12,960
But after all the fuss you made,

411
00:17:13,280 --> 00:17:14,641
it has served as a wake-up call.

412
00:17:19,161 --> 00:17:19,680
Actually,

413
00:17:20,081 --> 00:17:21,440
over these years,

414
00:17:22,361 --> 00:17:24,000
we know very well

415
00:17:24,081 --> 00:17:26,000
how you and Mr. Zheng have treated us.

416
00:17:26,040 --> 00:17:27,192
I really wasn't

417
00:17:27,480 --> 00:17:29,520
intentionally trying
to cause such a scene.

418
00:17:29,881 --> 00:17:30,440
Actually,

419
00:17:31,601 --> 00:17:32,561
I...

420
00:17:35,881 --> 00:17:37,480
Still don't trust Mr. Zheng and me?

421
00:17:38,280 --> 00:17:39,841
No, it's not that we don't trust you.

422
00:17:39,841 --> 00:17:40,792
It's not about trust.

423
00:17:41,200 --> 00:17:42,200
We're just afraid.

424
00:17:45,161 --> 00:17:46,264
We're afraid that

425
00:17:46,841 --> 00:17:48,056
if you and Mr. Zheng leave,

426
00:17:48,056 --> 00:17:49,304
what would we do?

427
00:17:49,641 --> 00:17:51,704
The project is only half-finished.

428
00:17:52,240 --> 00:17:53,641
What if nobody takes care of it?

429
00:17:53,641 --> 00:17:56,216
Others will continue the work
after we're gone.

430
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:57,520
No,

431
00:17:57,921 --> 00:17:58,680
it's not like that.

432
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:01,016
You and Mr. Zheng always keep your word.

433
00:18:01,760 --> 00:18:03,288
But what if others don't?

434
00:18:03,520 --> 00:18:04,680
What should we do then?

435
00:18:10,720 --> 00:18:11,384
Fatty.

436
00:18:11,881 --> 00:18:13,432
Thank you for your true thoughts.

437
00:18:15,121 --> 00:18:15,921
I understand.

438
00:18:17,960 --> 00:18:18,720
Take care.

439
00:18:23,561 --> 00:18:25,401
Wait, Ms. Li,

440
00:18:25,784 --> 00:18:28,056
you said those antiques are real.

441
00:18:28,056 --> 00:18:28,952
Really?

442
00:18:29,680 --> 00:18:30,240
Yes, they are.

443
00:18:31,641 --> 00:18:32,440
How is Changyuan?

444
00:18:33,040 --> 00:18:34,744
Fortunately, no bones were broken.

445
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:36,792
Dr. Hou said he'll be discharged soon.

446
00:18:38,280 --> 00:18:39,608
What did Mr. Xia say?

447
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:41,921
Don't mention it.

448
00:18:43,081 --> 00:18:44,440
He and Guan gave me an earful.

449
00:18:45,040 --> 00:18:46,720
They said we've abandoned our roots.

450
00:18:47,161 --> 00:18:49,240
And Mr. Xia gave me an ultimatum.

451
00:18:49,240 --> 00:18:50,200
If I can't get everyone

452
00:18:50,520 --> 00:18:52,376
to sign the agreements within a month,

453
00:18:52,740 --> 00:18:54,008
the project will be canceled.

454
00:18:55,480 --> 00:18:57,880
Obviously, this project

455
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:00,480
benefits Yuehai's future and its people.

456
00:19:01,081 --> 00:19:02,601
Why won't they just sign?

457
00:19:03,601 --> 00:19:06,104
After talking with Xuemei,
Fatty, and others,

458
00:19:06,200 --> 00:19:08,440
I realized they're all worried
about the same thing.

459
00:19:09,440 --> 00:19:10,081
What is it?

460
00:19:10,561 --> 00:19:12,248
We're betting on Yuehai's future.

461
00:19:12,921 --> 00:19:15,160
But the future is intangible to them.

462
00:19:15,601 --> 00:19:18,520
The only thing they can bet on is us.

463
00:19:23,240 --> 00:19:24,568
So we need to find a way

464
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:26,424
to show them

465
00:19:26,960 --> 00:19:29,000
we'll always be
in the same boat with them.

466
00:19:29,881 --> 00:19:31,352
I have an idea.

467
00:19:32,720 --> 00:19:33,848
The reporters are here.

468
00:19:38,440 --> 00:19:39,040
(Xie Chunlai, Li Qiuping)
Well,

469
00:19:39,121 --> 00:19:40,760
(Zheng Decheng, Tan Guangming, Lin Dongfu)
that's what I'll ask about later.

470
00:19:43,561 --> 00:19:44,536
So many people.

471
00:19:44,801 --> 00:19:45,601
Yes, six.

472
00:19:45,801 --> 00:19:46,561
Six cameras.

473
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:47,601
Xuemei.

474
00:19:48,088 --> 00:19:50,040
Can they record us too?

475
00:19:50,168 --> 00:19:52,040
Who knows?
Maybe everyone will be recorded.

476
00:19:52,280 --> 00:19:53,176
Quite a spectacle.

477
00:19:53,848 --> 00:19:58,720
(Xie Chunlai, Li Qiuping, Zheng Decheng,
Tan Guangming, Lin Dongfu)

478
00:19:58,720 --> 00:19:59,841
Good afternoon, everyone.

479
00:20:01,480 --> 00:20:02,081
Recently,

480
00:20:02,776 --> 00:20:05,656
the land expansion project

481
00:20:06,520 --> 00:20:07,864
has sparked

482
00:20:08,601 --> 00:20:10,121
discussion and controversy.

483
00:20:10,480 --> 00:20:12,568
(Li Qiuping, Zheng Decheng)
We invited you today

484
00:20:12,960 --> 00:20:15,200
to speak from the heart.

485
00:20:15,801 --> 00:20:18,440
We've also invited journalists
from Pingchuan County.

486
00:20:21,801 --> 00:20:24,081
Our words today

487
00:20:24,081 --> 00:20:25,112
represent

488
00:20:25,601 --> 00:20:28,121
all Yuehai Town cadres,

489
00:20:29,240 --> 00:20:30,328
and will be documented.

490
00:20:30,841 --> 00:20:33,976
People across the county,
even the whole province,

491
00:20:34,321 --> 00:20:35,096
will see this.

492
00:20:37,656 --> 00:20:38,361
Will we be on TV?

493
00:20:38,881 --> 00:20:40,440
Who knows?

494
00:20:42,480 --> 00:20:43,256
First,

495
00:20:44,280 --> 00:20:45,752
I want to apologize.

496
00:20:47,520 --> 00:20:49,400
Regarding the land expansion project,

497
00:20:49,520 --> 00:20:52,600
(Li Qiuping)
we didn't plan thoroughly enough.

498
00:20:53,361 --> 00:20:54,616
We believed

499
00:20:55,121 --> 00:20:57,944
that anything,
for Yuehai's long-term development,

500
00:20:58,280 --> 00:21:00,856
should be resolutely implemented.

501
00:21:02,440 --> 00:21:03,192
However,

502
00:21:04,121 --> 00:21:05,440
we failed

503
00:21:06,121 --> 00:21:09,401
to think of your real feelings
and needs.

504
00:21:09,921 --> 00:21:12,161
This caused intense insecurity.

505
00:21:12,760 --> 00:21:15,720
We sincerely apologize for this.

506
00:21:18,321 --> 00:21:19,480
Do you feel secure?

507
00:21:19,921 --> 00:21:20,952
Are they serious?

508
00:21:21,121 --> 00:21:22,520
Mr. Zheng, Ms. Li,

509
00:21:23,121 --> 00:21:24,200
as you said,

510
00:21:24,361 --> 00:21:25,688
you initiated this project

511
00:21:25,841 --> 00:21:28,152
due to Yuehai's land shortage.

512
00:21:28,641 --> 00:21:31,161
But for a town
to undertake such a project,

513
00:21:31,161 --> 00:21:33,000
isn't it somewhat grandiose?

514
00:21:33,280 --> 00:21:35,801
Some form of the leadership's vanity
for achievements?

515
00:21:39,200 --> 00:21:41,944
This vanity for achievements
you're talking about

516
00:21:42,240 --> 00:21:44,088
is definitely not what we want.

517
00:21:44,641 --> 00:21:46,680
We persist in doing this

518
00:21:46,960 --> 00:21:47,641
because

519
00:21:48,760 --> 00:21:49,816
the land is gone.

520
00:21:50,801 --> 00:21:51,512
This matter

521
00:21:52,280 --> 00:21:55,288
has hindered Yuehai's development

522
00:21:55,601 --> 00:21:56,344
and its future.

523
00:21:57,641 --> 00:21:58,616
Someone

524
00:21:59,040 --> 00:22:00,561
has to stand up to do this thing.

525
00:22:01,161 --> 00:22:02,200
And someone

526
00:22:02,841 --> 00:22:05,144
has to take responsibility

527
00:22:05,520 --> 00:22:06,520
for it.

528
00:22:07,161 --> 00:22:08,000
So, we believe

529
00:22:08,401 --> 00:22:12,121
that for the residents of Yuehai
and its future development,

530
00:22:12,921 --> 00:22:14,008
we must do it.

531
00:22:14,960 --> 00:22:16,376
We must do it immediately.

532
00:22:16,921 --> 00:22:19,032
We have to make it a success.

533
00:22:21,161 --> 00:22:22,904
Most people might think

534
00:22:22,904 --> 00:22:23,801
that we as cadres

535
00:22:24,121 --> 00:22:25,321
just need to create results

536
00:22:25,520 --> 00:22:27,641
and leave Yuehai once our term ends

537
00:22:28,040 --> 00:22:29,240
or get promoted.

538
00:22:29,881 --> 00:22:31,544
Someone asked me a question.

539
00:22:32,344 --> 00:22:34,424
Three years of expansion,
two years of consolidation.

540
00:22:34,760 --> 00:22:38,200
Will you still be
in Yuehai after five years?

541
00:22:44,161 --> 00:22:47,000
I can now firmly answer this question.

542
00:22:48,040 --> 00:22:49,208
Five years later,

543
00:22:49,720 --> 00:22:51,480
I, Li Qiuping, will still be here.

544
00:22:52,720 --> 00:22:55,064
We've submitted an application
to our superiors.

545
00:22:55,720 --> 00:22:59,000
We'll stay in our current positions
until the project is completed.

546
00:22:59,960 --> 00:23:01,720
This project was proposed by me.

547
00:23:02,680 --> 00:23:04,920
I'll definitely not give up halfway.

548
00:23:05,921 --> 00:23:07,928
Right here, I, Zheng Decheng,

549
00:23:08,921 --> 00:23:11,128
(Zheng Decheng)
solemnly promise to everyone present

550
00:23:11,680 --> 00:23:15,040
and to the residents of Yuehai Town

551
00:23:15,520 --> 00:23:16,121
watching on TV

552
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:18,264
that until the project is done,

553
00:23:19,121 --> 00:23:20,024
I will not

554
00:23:20,881 --> 00:23:22,081
leave Yuehai.

555
00:23:26,641 --> 00:23:29,752
Yuehai is my home, too.

556
00:23:30,680 --> 00:23:33,280
Binhai Road is also my home.

557
00:23:35,321 --> 00:23:38,840
I, Xie Chunlai, won't go anywhere

558
00:23:39,800 --> 00:23:41,816
until this project is finished.

559
00:23:46,601 --> 00:23:50,264
(Lin Dongfu)
As the deputy mayor in charge of the project,

560
00:23:51,200 --> 00:23:53,641
I, Lin Dongfu,
won't leave until this project

561
00:23:54,121 --> 00:23:54,904
is completed.

562
00:23:54,904 --> 00:23:55,864
I can't leave.

563
00:23:57,841 --> 00:23:59,064
(Li Qiuping, Zheng Decheng, Tan Guangming)
I, Tan Guangming,

564
00:23:59,361 --> 00:24:01,336
(Lin Dongfu)
primarily oversee finance.

565
00:24:01,601 --> 00:24:03,512
I need to manage the funds well.

566
00:24:04,120 --> 00:24:05,944
I can't overspend or waste money.

567
00:24:08,280 --> 00:24:09,304
I also won't leave.

568
00:24:11,288 --> 00:24:12,728
Are they serious?

569
00:24:13,368 --> 00:24:15,000
Just listen. Are they crazy?

570
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:15,641
Will they quit?

571
00:24:15,700 --> 00:24:16,200
Right?

572
00:24:16,200 --> 00:24:18,000
In front of the media,
how can it be fake?

573
00:24:18,401 --> 00:24:19,561
Think about it.

574
00:24:19,561 --> 00:24:20,121
Be quiet.

575
00:24:20,240 --> 00:24:21,720
I'll donate to you.

576
00:24:21,720 --> 00:24:22,808
Hello, I have a question.

577
00:24:27,321 --> 00:24:29,321
You can publicly make such a commitment,

578
00:24:29,321 --> 00:24:30,168
and I admire it.

579
00:24:30,760 --> 00:24:32,081
(Xie Chunlai, Li Qiuping, Zheng Decheng)
I have one last question.

580
00:24:32,361 --> 00:24:33,784
(Tan Guangming, Lin Dongfu)
Yuehai is just a town.

581
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:35,896
It has its scale and limit,

582
00:24:36,200 --> 00:24:38,361
and the risks and costs
of the expansion project

583
00:24:38,361 --> 00:24:40,216
have far exceeded this limit.

584
00:24:40,361 --> 00:24:42,200
Is it really necessary

585
00:24:42,321 --> 00:24:43,704
to do something impossible?

586
00:24:45,432 --> 00:24:48,504
(Xie Chunlai, Li Qiuping, Zheng Decheng,
Tan Guangming, Lin Dongfu)

587
00:24:50,776 --> 00:24:52,161
(Li Qiuping,
Zheng Decheng, Tan Guangming)

588
00:24:52,161 --> 00:24:53,240
Almost everyone

589
00:24:53,881 --> 00:24:55,160
we know

590
00:24:56,000 --> 00:24:56,760
believes

591
00:24:57,401 --> 00:24:58,264
that it's a fantasy

592
00:24:59,081 --> 00:25:00,152
for a town

593
00:25:00,960 --> 00:25:02,104
to complete expansion.

594
00:25:03,561 --> 00:25:04,720
They kindly advise us

595
00:25:05,601 --> 00:25:06,361
to give up.

596
00:25:08,161 --> 00:25:10,520
So, why not?

597
00:25:13,641 --> 00:25:15,800
We've never thought about giving up.

598
00:25:16,161 --> 00:25:17,680
We will only strive hard.

599
00:25:21,040 --> 00:25:21,540
Well said!

600
00:25:49,208 --> 00:25:50,584
Mom.

601
00:25:51,121 --> 00:25:53,176
Keep it down!

602
00:25:53,480 --> 00:25:54,601
Your dad is sleeping.

603
00:25:55,200 --> 00:25:55,881
It's time to go.

604
00:25:55,881 --> 00:25:57,680
Okay. You go ahead.
I'll be there shortly.

605
00:25:57,680 --> 00:25:58,648
Hurry up then.

606
00:25:58,648 --> 00:25:59,672
I know. Go ahead.

607
00:25:59,940 --> 00:26:01,208
Wait, is this okay?

608
00:26:01,208 --> 00:26:02,168
It looks good.

609
00:26:02,168 --> 00:26:03,121
- See you later.
- Okay.

610
00:26:03,121 --> 00:26:03,720
- Take it easy.
- Okay.

611
00:26:23,561 --> 00:26:24,240
You're awake.

612
00:26:35,760 --> 00:26:36,920
What are you doing?

613
00:26:38,712 --> 00:26:39,720
Back off!

614
00:26:44,200 --> 00:26:45,081
My legs feel weak.

615
00:26:46,081 --> 00:26:47,448
Why did I fall asleep here?

616
00:26:48,024 --> 00:26:48,881
Where are you going?

617
00:26:48,881 --> 00:26:49,848
I have to go.

618
00:26:49,960 --> 00:26:50,460
Wait.

619
00:26:50,801 --> 00:26:52,024
I haven't even talked to you.

620
00:26:52,024 --> 00:26:52,760
You can't leave.

621
00:26:52,921 --> 00:26:53,912
You called me here?

622
00:26:54,801 --> 00:26:55,801
Why didn't you wake me?

623
00:26:55,801 --> 00:26:56,801
I fell asleep here.

624
00:26:57,040 --> 00:26:57,752
What is it?

625
00:27:14,401 --> 00:27:15,000
Take a look.

626
00:27:15,601 --> 00:27:17,176
I told you. I didn't want the money.

627
00:27:18,440 --> 00:27:20,568
It's not for you. I want you to see it.

628
00:27:23,561 --> 00:27:25,401
You think
I don't know how much money we have?

629
00:27:25,401 --> 00:27:26,872
I don't need to check it out.

630
00:27:28,000 --> 00:27:28,601
You sure?

631
00:27:33,272 --> 00:27:33,912
You...

632
00:27:35,881 --> 00:27:36,856
Check or not?

633
00:27:36,856 --> 00:27:38,104
No need.

634
00:27:38,280 --> 00:27:40,000
Fine, I asked you.
You didn't want to look.

635
00:28:10,200 --> 00:28:13,176
Half of this money was originally yours.

636
00:28:13,361 --> 00:28:14,648
But you refused it yourself.

637
00:28:19,921 --> 00:28:20,720
Regretting it now?

638
00:28:22,841 --> 00:28:24,536
Still think money is worthless?

639
00:28:28,344 --> 00:28:29,496
We have over ten million.

640
00:28:30,480 --> 00:28:31,288
Regretting it now?

641
00:28:34,921 --> 00:28:36,280
What do you mean by this?

642
00:28:37,641 --> 00:28:38,680
You called me here

643
00:28:39,440 --> 00:28:40,536
just to see me regret it?

644
00:28:49,336 --> 00:28:51,200
(Party A: Li Qiuping,
Party B: Gao Xuemei)

645
00:28:51,200 --> 00:28:52,120
You've figured it out.

646
00:28:54,960 --> 00:28:56,040
Good for you.

647
00:28:58,081 --> 00:28:59,608
Holding out would've been a bad look.

648
00:29:00,000 --> 00:29:01,336
After the press conference,

649
00:29:02,040 --> 00:29:03,321
over 100 people decided to move.

650
00:29:03,841 --> 00:29:04,921
You think I don't know?

651
00:29:05,200 --> 00:29:06,480
Some haven't moved yet.

652
00:29:06,841 --> 00:29:07,520
They'll move.

653
00:29:09,720 --> 00:29:10,680
Signing this contract

654
00:29:11,801 --> 00:29:12,601
is commendable.

655
00:29:13,361 --> 00:29:14,456
But it doesn't cost money.

656
00:29:14,760 --> 00:29:17,040
Why did you put up all this money?

657
00:29:19,200 --> 00:29:20,792
I want to help the town government.

658
00:29:21,720 --> 00:29:23,000
You want to backstop it?

659
00:29:26,161 --> 00:29:27,121
I haven't decided yet.

660
00:29:28,841 --> 00:29:32,760
Out of this ten million,
three million is a loan.

661
00:29:34,040 --> 00:29:35,832
All these years of hard work,

662
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:39,064
if I invest all of it in this,

663
00:29:40,121 --> 00:29:40,921
do you think

664
00:29:43,881 --> 00:29:44,760
it's worth it?

665
00:29:47,601 --> 00:29:50,136
So you want me to help you decide?

666
00:29:54,321 --> 00:29:56,632
I never asked your opinion
on big decisions before.

667
00:29:57,440 --> 00:29:58,561
I'm giving you a chance.

668
00:29:58,960 --> 00:30:00,200
Whatever you say goes.

669
00:30:12,520 --> 00:30:13,432
Do you remember

670
00:30:14,841 --> 00:30:16,728
what you said during the typhoon?

671
00:30:22,280 --> 00:30:23,224
Who is there?

672
00:30:24,121 --> 00:30:24,760
Gao Xuemei!

673
00:30:26,161 --> 00:30:28,152
Stop pulling me! Let go!

674
00:30:28,561 --> 00:30:31,288
The typhoon's coming, Gao Xuemei!

675
00:30:32,081 --> 00:30:34,392
That boat is tied securely.

676
00:30:34,760 --> 00:30:35,480
Xie.

677
00:30:36,440 --> 00:30:38,264
It's so hard for us to get

678
00:30:38,720 --> 00:30:39,832
where we are now.

679
00:30:40,361 --> 00:30:41,720
We've had it so tough.

680
00:30:43,161 --> 00:30:45,528
No way back means only a way out,
understand?

681
00:30:46,280 --> 00:30:48,000
No way back means only a way out.

682
00:30:52,081 --> 00:30:53,528
So I'll listen to you.

683
00:30:56,881 --> 00:30:57,520
Let's gamble.

684
00:30:58,401 --> 00:30:59,768
If you lose, I'm here for you.

685
00:31:01,824 --> 00:31:06,118
♪Your silhouette
still lingers before my eyes♪

686
00:31:06,311 --> 00:31:09,464
♪Your promise is deep in my heart♪

687
00:31:10,656 --> 00:31:12,888
♪Remembering your tenderness♪

688
00:31:12,888 --> 00:31:17,592
♪Memories won't let me go♪

689
00:31:19,527 --> 00:31:23,601
♪You're the gentle passage of a book♪

690
00:31:23,601 --> 00:31:27,064
♪Sweeping me away like a gust of wind♪

691
00:31:27,064 --> 00:31:28,536
You know what I dreamed

692
00:31:29,480 --> 00:31:30,872
when I fell asleep there?

693
00:31:31,200 --> 00:31:31,700
What?

694
00:31:32,280 --> 00:31:33,496
A big peacock.

695
00:31:34,121 --> 00:31:35,160
It had her feathers open.

696
00:31:36,480 --> 00:31:37,144
I'm serious.

697
00:31:40,161 --> 00:31:41,720
Alright. Let me buy you dinner tonight.

698
00:31:42,081 --> 00:31:43,128
I might not be free.

699
00:31:45,760 --> 00:31:47,032
Well, you've been told.

700
00:31:47,561 --> 00:31:48,376
And Xiaoyu.

701
00:31:48,720 --> 00:31:50,801
Her boyfriend invited me to dinner.

702
00:31:50,801 --> 00:31:51,520
Are you coming?

703
00:31:51,520 --> 00:31:52,376
Whose boyfriend?

704
00:31:52,921 --> 00:31:54,136
Xiaoyu has a boyfriend?

705
00:31:54,520 --> 00:31:55,520
How come I didn't know?

706
00:31:55,520 --> 00:31:56,792
I'm telling you right now.

707
00:31:56,980 --> 00:31:58,720
Why am I always the last
to know everything

708
00:31:58,720 --> 00:31:59,641
in our family?

709
00:31:59,720 --> 00:32:01,016
I don't know about our money.

710
00:32:01,161 --> 00:32:02,104
Xiaoyu has a boyfriend.

711
00:32:02,104 --> 00:32:03,520
W-When did this happen?

712
00:32:03,801 --> 00:32:04,568
Did she invite me?

713
00:32:04,841 --> 00:32:06,328
I'm just asking if you're going.

714
00:32:24,760 --> 00:32:25,752
Dishes are all served.

715
00:32:29,321 --> 00:32:30,081
Enjoy your meal.

716
00:32:48,472 --> 00:32:49,176
Right.

717
00:32:50,440 --> 00:32:51,480
Mom, Dad,

718
00:32:52,200 --> 00:32:52,881
this is...

719
00:32:54,361 --> 00:32:55,128
Wrong.

720
00:32:55,361 --> 00:32:56,376
Mr. Xie, Ms. Gao.

721
00:32:57,801 --> 00:32:59,040
Too early to call you that way.

722
00:32:59,440 --> 00:32:59,960
Well...

723
00:32:59,960 --> 00:33:00,921
- Relax.
- Mr. Xie, Ms. Gao.

724
00:33:01,752 --> 00:33:02,904
I'm too nervous. I misspoke.

725
00:33:03,224 --> 00:33:03,992
It's okay.

726
00:33:04,240 --> 00:33:04,792
Alright.

727
00:33:04,792 --> 00:33:05,421
Just a little.

728
00:33:05,921 --> 00:33:07,240
This isn't sweet, right?

729
00:33:07,240 --> 00:33:07,740
Not sweet.

730
00:33:07,760 --> 00:33:08,888
He can't drink sweet things.

731
00:33:09,081 --> 00:33:09,760
It's spicy.

732
00:33:10,561 --> 00:33:11,841
Okay, less. That's fine.

733
00:33:11,960 --> 00:33:12,536
Alright.

734
00:33:15,161 --> 00:33:16,056
Just a little for you.

735
00:33:16,321 --> 00:33:16,960
Thanks.

736
00:33:17,520 --> 00:33:18,232
Not at all.

737
00:33:20,040 --> 00:33:21,336
I brought this from my hometown.

738
00:33:21,976 --> 00:33:23,352
My parents specifically asked me

739
00:33:23,641 --> 00:33:25,208
to bring it for you.

740
00:33:26,200 --> 00:33:26,760
Aged liquor.

741
00:33:29,520 --> 00:33:30,020
Is it good?

742
00:33:30,040 --> 00:33:30,540
Not bad.

743
00:33:31,161 --> 00:33:32,120
Hope you like it.

744
00:33:33,561 --> 00:33:34,264
Too spicy.

745
00:33:34,401 --> 00:33:35,288
A bit spicy.

746
00:33:35,561 --> 00:33:36,472
Smells good.

747
00:33:42,280 --> 00:33:42,780
Well,

748
00:33:43,520 --> 00:33:44,792
I'd like to propose a toast.

749
00:33:47,641 --> 00:33:48,568
He can hold his liquor.

750
00:33:48,641 --> 00:33:49,141
Drink less.

751
00:33:49,680 --> 00:33:50,841
If he drinks too much,

752
00:33:51,121 --> 00:33:52,152
he might become frank.

753
00:33:53,480 --> 00:33:54,361
How long?

754
00:33:58,601 --> 00:33:59,101
Mr. Xie.

755
00:34:02,040 --> 00:34:03,160
Xiaoyu and I haven't

756
00:34:03,720 --> 00:34:04,641
known each other long,

757
00:34:06,040 --> 00:34:07,161
but we're serious.

758
00:34:08,960 --> 00:34:10,840
Xiaoyu is simple.

759
00:34:12,281 --> 00:34:14,136
She doesn't play tricks.

760
00:34:14,321 --> 00:34:14,821
Yes.

761
00:34:14,841 --> 00:34:15,881
She is innocent.

762
00:34:15,881 --> 00:34:16,824
Yes, she is.

763
00:34:17,040 --> 00:34:18,904
Has she told you everything
about the family?

764
00:34:20,080 --> 00:34:21,120
You know it all now,

765
00:34:21,120 --> 00:34:21,960
don't you?

766
00:34:24,401 --> 00:34:25,040
Sure.

767
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:31,800
Mr. Xie, Ms. Gao,

768
00:34:33,761 --> 00:34:35,064
to be honest,

769
00:34:35,440 --> 00:34:36,536
at the beginning,

770
00:34:37,201 --> 00:34:38,360
I was a bit bothered.

771
00:34:39,241 --> 00:34:40,040
I know

772
00:34:40,361 --> 00:34:42,168
your family is famously wealthy
in Yuehai.

773
00:34:43,120 --> 00:34:45,112
When Xiaoyu and I first started dating,

774
00:34:45,681 --> 00:34:47,256
people kept making snide remarks,

775
00:34:48,401 --> 00:34:49,976
saying I liked her for her money.

776
00:34:50,841 --> 00:34:52,600
I've studied hard since I was a kid.

777
00:34:52,841 --> 00:34:54,296
I just want to show everyone

778
00:34:54,640 --> 00:34:55,864
that with my own ability,

779
00:34:56,281 --> 00:34:57,960
I can make my own success.

780
00:34:58,281 --> 00:34:59,480
I want to succeed on my own.

781
00:35:00,281 --> 00:35:01,241
My name implies my hope.

782
00:35:01,761 --> 00:35:02,281
Yang Fan.

783
00:35:03,040 --> 00:35:03,681
Set sail.

784
00:35:06,801 --> 00:35:07,440
Fan.

785
00:35:07,440 --> 00:35:08,728
- Good for you.
- Very good.

786
00:35:08,881 --> 00:35:09,432
I'm serious.

787
00:35:09,881 --> 00:35:10,936
You're going to set sail,

788
00:35:10,936 --> 00:35:12,088
and then the storm hits.

789
00:35:12,160 --> 00:35:12,660
Right?

790
00:35:13,000 --> 00:35:14,104
Yes, true.

791
00:35:14,361 --> 00:35:15,064
You tell him.

792
00:35:15,480 --> 00:35:16,040
You say it.

793
00:35:16,201 --> 00:35:19,160
- Me? You say. You are her dad.
- Me? You say.

794
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:20,952
You are her dad.

795
00:35:20,952 --> 00:35:22,761
- You say it.
- It's good news.

796
00:35:22,872 --> 00:35:24,408
It's the first time meeting him.

797
00:35:24,408 --> 00:35:25,681
- Is it appropriate?
- He might have concerns.

798
00:35:25,921 --> 00:35:27,480
- Don't make him worry.
- You're right.

799
00:35:27,600 --> 00:35:29,160
I'm saying it right now.

800
00:35:29,241 --> 00:35:30,761
- Xiaoyu doesn't know it either.
- Yes.

801
00:35:30,840 --> 00:35:32,000
- Right?
- Well...

802
00:35:32,000 --> 00:35:32,600
It's okay.

803
00:35:32,841 --> 00:35:33,341
Go ahead.

804
00:35:33,440 --> 00:35:33,940
It's fine.

805
00:35:33,960 --> 00:35:35,864
Something has happened in our family.

806
00:35:35,864 --> 00:35:37,464
We haven't told Xiaoyu yet.

807
00:35:38,201 --> 00:35:40,281
Today is an opportunity to say it.

808
00:35:43,080 --> 00:35:44,856
We've put all of our money

809
00:35:44,856 --> 00:35:46,968
into the project in Yuehai.

810
00:35:47,401 --> 00:35:49,080
Now, there's not a penny left at home.

811
00:35:49,560 --> 00:35:50,456
We still owe

812
00:35:51,000 --> 00:35:52,152
3,000,000 in loans.

813
00:35:52,321 --> 00:35:52,841
3,000,000?

814
00:35:53,201 --> 00:35:53,701
Yes.

815
00:35:53,921 --> 00:35:54,480
Three million.

816
00:35:55,361 --> 00:35:56,888
From now on, we might have to

817
00:35:57,040 --> 00:35:58,264
live a hard life

818
00:35:58,440 --> 00:35:59,704
and tighten our belts.

819
00:35:59,881 --> 00:36:01,440
Look, you've scared them.

820
00:36:01,600 --> 00:36:03,160
- But this is good news!
- Yeah.

821
00:36:03,320 --> 00:36:05,681
Actually, we were worried at the start.

822
00:36:06,000 --> 00:36:07,512
But after what you just said,

823
00:36:07,800 --> 00:36:08,984
we're not worried now.

824
00:36:09,801 --> 00:36:10,361
Yang.

825
00:36:10,840 --> 00:36:12,216
- Starting today,
- What's going on?

826
00:36:12,216 --> 00:36:13,656
you'll embark on your journey

827
00:36:14,080 --> 00:36:15,032
from our home.

828
00:36:15,321 --> 00:36:15,960
Okay?

829
00:36:17,281 --> 00:36:18,328
This is good news!

830
00:36:25,520 --> 00:36:26,401
Let's drink.

831
00:36:26,401 --> 00:36:27,480
- Come on.
- Come on.

832
00:36:27,480 --> 00:36:28,281
Let's celebrate!

833
00:36:29,020 --> 00:36:31,361
Mom, can you be serious?

834
00:36:31,416 --> 00:36:33,624
Can you stop joking around?

835
00:36:33,624 --> 00:36:35,321
- She is serious.
- Yes.

836
00:36:35,401 --> 00:36:37,480
I never joke about big matters.
Don't be silly.

837
00:36:40,040 --> 00:36:41,500
No matter who you are,

838
00:36:41,600 --> 00:36:43,704
just be ready to weather the storm.

839
00:36:43,801 --> 00:36:44,321
Yes.

840
00:36:44,520 --> 00:36:46,520
I honestly don't think
you need to worry too much.

841
00:36:46,761 --> 00:36:47,960
A hard life will end

842
00:36:47,960 --> 00:36:50,120
in seven or eight years.

843
00:36:53,881 --> 00:36:55,416
- I'm not scaring them.
- Seven or eight years?

844
00:36:55,864 --> 00:36:56,888
It would take a decade.

845
00:36:57,080 --> 00:36:58,424
I think if we work hard

846
00:36:58,424 --> 00:36:59,448
together,

847
00:36:59,640 --> 00:37:01,040
if we stick together,

848
00:37:01,040 --> 00:37:02,488
it'll take seven or eight years.

849
00:37:02,904 --> 00:37:04,952
As for the worst-case scenario,

850
00:37:04,952 --> 00:37:06,321
we'll do our absolute best.

851
00:37:06,321 --> 00:37:06,821
Agreed?

852
00:37:06,968 --> 00:37:09,620
- We can't order expensive food anymore.
- Take it to go.

853
00:37:09,681 --> 00:37:10,620
Look at this meat.

854
00:37:10,620 --> 00:37:11,160
Look.

855
00:37:11,160 --> 00:37:12,361
Let's not eat this now.

856
00:37:12,361 --> 00:37:13,304
Save it for tonight.

857
00:37:13,688 --> 00:37:15,000
- I'm done yet.
- Take it to go.

858
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:16,824
- Take it to go.
- I put food on your plate.

859
00:37:17,272 --> 00:37:19,288
Then have mine, okay?

860
00:37:19,768 --> 00:37:20,281
Eat up.

861
00:37:20,281 --> 00:37:21,960
- Help yourself.
- Okay.

862
00:37:21,960 --> 00:37:22,460
Sure.

863
00:37:22,640 --> 00:37:23,241
Help yourself.

864
00:37:24,344 --> 00:37:25,656
We really can't waste anything.

865
00:37:25,656 --> 00:37:26,776
You can't be free-handed.

866
00:37:28,841 --> 00:37:30,401
Come on. Help yourselves.

867
00:37:34,440 --> 00:37:35,040
Well,

868
00:37:35,480 --> 00:37:36,376
Mr. Xie, Ms. Gao,

869
00:37:36,681 --> 00:37:37,241
Xiaoyu,

870
00:37:38,040 --> 00:37:40,160
I just remembered
I have something else to do.

871
00:37:40,721 --> 00:37:43,160
I think I have a meeting
to attend back at the factory.

872
00:37:43,841 --> 00:37:44,341
Well,

873
00:37:44,841 --> 00:37:46,040
you work at the wire factory?

874
00:37:46,040 --> 00:37:46,840
Yes.

875
00:37:46,960 --> 00:37:48,152
It's about to be demolished.

876
00:37:48,152 --> 00:37:49,120
I know your boss.

877
00:37:49,944 --> 00:37:50,840
I can get you the day.

878
00:37:50,840 --> 00:37:51,841
No, no need.

879
00:37:51,841 --> 00:37:53,176
- No.
- Don't miss this big meal.

880
00:37:53,176 --> 00:37:54,000
No, no need.

881
00:37:54,072 --> 00:37:54,904
No need.

882
00:37:54,904 --> 00:37:57,881
I'm young and should focus on my career.

883
00:37:57,881 --> 00:37:58,401
Right?

884
00:37:59,000 --> 00:38:00,281
I'll finish my drink first.

885
00:38:01,401 --> 00:38:03,761
Finish dinner before you go.
Why the rush?

886
00:38:03,761 --> 00:38:04,952
No need. I've drunk my fill.

887
00:38:05,720 --> 00:38:07,352
Are you leaving? Take the liquor.

888
00:38:13,881 --> 00:38:15,000
This bottle's already open.

889
00:38:15,000 --> 00:38:16,312
I'll take this unopened one.

890
00:38:22,281 --> 00:38:22,881
Yang Fan.

891
00:38:27,640 --> 00:38:29,688
- Mom, what did he mean?
- He is not into our Xiaoyu.

892
00:38:29,881 --> 00:38:31,841
Indeed. Yang Fan? He...

893
00:38:31,841 --> 00:38:33,080
More like "Shipwreck" Fan.

894
00:38:33,160 --> 00:38:34,616
What were you talking about earlier?

895
00:38:34,721 --> 00:38:37,361
Why don't you two just throw me
into the sea?

896
00:38:37,432 --> 00:38:39,096
What are you talking about?

897
00:38:39,160 --> 00:38:39,881
Listen,

898
00:38:40,504 --> 00:38:41,400
on this matter,

899
00:38:41,400 --> 00:38:42,360
listen to me.

900
00:38:42,440 --> 00:38:44,440
Look, this guy

901
00:38:44,440 --> 00:38:45,240
isn't the right one.

902
00:38:45,361 --> 00:38:46,264
Just let him go.

903
00:38:46,801 --> 00:38:48,568
- Mom.
- You deserve better.

904
00:38:48,960 --> 00:38:50,648
Sweetie, you'll meet the right one.

905
00:38:50,761 --> 00:38:51,281
Okay?

906
00:38:51,721 --> 00:38:53,440
You should learn from your mom on this.

907
00:38:53,560 --> 00:38:55,576
See how well your mom picked a man?

908
00:38:55,721 --> 00:38:56,281
Right?

909
00:38:57,201 --> 00:38:57,721
Well,

910
00:38:58,120 --> 00:38:59,841
that boy has a smug look.

911
00:38:59,841 --> 00:39:00,960
He is unreliable.

912
00:39:01,241 --> 00:39:03,064
Just shut up.

913
00:39:03,320 --> 00:39:04,792
- She is upset.
- Okay.

914
00:39:05,321 --> 00:39:07,640
Once you have a boyfriend again,

915
00:39:07,640 --> 00:39:09,400
bring him home to show your dad first.

916
00:39:09,520 --> 00:39:11,841
Your dad isn't foolish
about major matters.

917
00:39:12,281 --> 00:39:13,336
Cheer up.

918
00:39:14,921 --> 00:39:15,520
Mom.

919
00:39:16,600 --> 00:39:17,100
Dad.

920
00:39:18,160 --> 00:39:18,660
Well...

921
00:39:19,480 --> 00:39:20,920
Ten years? Seriously?

922
00:39:29,321 --> 00:39:30,680
Do you know what this is?

923
00:39:31,160 --> 00:39:31,761
See?

924
00:39:32,000 --> 00:39:33,016
This is imported.

925
00:39:33,600 --> 00:39:37,080
This is X Zero.

926
00:39:37,361 --> 00:39:38,744
It's called XO.

927
00:39:40,241 --> 00:39:40,921
Same.

928
00:39:41,120 --> 00:39:42,040
Look,

929
00:39:42,040 --> 00:39:43,192
do you know my favorite?

930
00:39:43,401 --> 00:39:45,240
My favorite drink is 'Hisway'.

931
00:39:45,520 --> 00:39:46,201
Whiskey.

932
00:39:46,480 --> 00:39:47,201
What's this wine?

933
00:39:47,241 --> 00:39:48,120
It's what you said.

934
00:39:48,120 --> 00:39:48,801
Hello, Ms. Gao.

935
00:39:48,881 --> 00:39:49,761
Hello.

936
00:39:49,801 --> 00:39:50,640
- Ms. Gao.
- Ms. Gao.

937
00:39:50,681 --> 00:39:51,520
Hello.

938
00:39:52,000 --> 00:39:52,500
Hello.

939
00:39:53,600 --> 00:39:54,401
Take it!

940
00:39:54,600 --> 00:39:55,768
One for everyone.

941
00:39:55,768 --> 00:39:57,000
- Everyone gets one.
- Okay.

942
00:39:57,000 --> 00:39:58,072
- Speaking English?
- Give me a hand.

943
00:39:58,072 --> 00:39:58,648
Come on.

944
00:39:58,648 --> 00:39:59,736
I've had overseas orders.

945
00:40:00,321 --> 00:40:01,592
Like instruction manuals,

946
00:40:01,761 --> 00:40:03,096
- in Arabic.
- Here.

947
00:40:03,480 --> 00:40:04,321
Just wait.

948
00:40:06,201 --> 00:40:07,352
You all haven't

949
00:40:07,352 --> 00:40:08,888
signed the relocation agreement.

950
00:40:09,520 --> 00:40:10,520
Embarrassing, isn't it?

951
00:40:12,241 --> 00:40:14,680
Including myself,
33 businesses in total.

952
00:40:15,040 --> 00:40:15,560
Come on.

953
00:40:16,080 --> 00:40:17,720
Let's all finish this drink first.

954
00:40:17,921 --> 00:40:19,100
Then, we can talk, okay?

955
00:40:19,600 --> 00:40:20,100
- Okay.
- Cheers.

956
00:40:20,241 --> 00:40:21,080
Bottoms up!

957
00:40:21,080 --> 00:40:21,580
Come on.

958
00:40:21,640 --> 00:40:22,281
Come on.

959
00:40:27,160 --> 00:40:27,896
You don't drink?

960
00:40:28,600 --> 00:40:29,816
I overdid it last night.

961
00:40:38,120 --> 00:40:38,681
Brandy.

962
00:40:38,721 --> 00:40:39,221
Here.

963
00:40:45,080 --> 00:40:45,640
Ms. Gao,

964
00:40:46,440 --> 00:40:47,736
you called all of us here today

965
00:40:47,736 --> 00:40:48,920
just to help the government

966
00:40:49,040 --> 00:40:50,600
persuade us?

967
00:40:50,600 --> 00:40:51,352
A Persuader?

968
00:40:53,921 --> 00:40:54,421
Exactly.

969
00:40:54,480 --> 00:40:55,241
This is

970
00:40:55,681 --> 00:40:58,801
the relocation agreement.

971
00:40:59,201 --> 00:41:00,760
For a hundred-square-meter shop,

972
00:41:00,921 --> 00:41:01,761
after the expansion,

973
00:41:01,761 --> 00:41:03,640
the town will
give you 200 square meters back.

974
00:41:03,640 --> 00:41:05,400
What's the property price in Yuehai now?

975
00:41:05,400 --> 00:41:06,584
I think everyone here

976
00:41:06,584 --> 00:41:07,841
knows better than I do.

977
00:41:08,160 --> 00:41:09,848
This is a good deal, actually.

978
00:41:10,994 --> 00:41:11,553
Changyuan,

979
00:41:12,193 --> 00:41:12,693
signing?

980
00:41:15,394 --> 00:41:16,481
I...

981
00:41:18,177 --> 00:41:19,689
I-I need to think about it some more.

982
00:41:19,849 --> 00:41:20,530
Let me think.

983
00:41:23,170 --> 00:41:23,729
Ms. Gao,

984
00:41:24,650 --> 00:41:25,570
here's how I see it.

985
00:41:26,066 --> 00:41:28,626
Whether 200 or 500 square meters,

986
00:41:29,026 --> 00:41:30,347
it's virtual.

987
00:41:30,546 --> 00:41:31,066
Right?

988
00:41:31,546 --> 00:41:33,186
Cash is real.

989
00:41:33,387 --> 00:41:35,594
- Exactly.
- Yeah!

990
00:41:36,186 --> 00:41:38,066
Even if we could get paid twice,

991
00:41:38,427 --> 00:41:39,467
we'd have to wait years.

992
00:41:39,867 --> 00:41:41,290
H-Hold on.

993
00:41:41,290 --> 00:41:42,226
I haven't finished yet.

994
00:41:43,347 --> 00:41:45,106
For those who don't want this agreement,

995
00:41:45,747 --> 00:41:46,506
look,

996
00:41:46,827 --> 00:41:48,347
there's another agreement here.

997
00:41:49,106 --> 00:41:50,267
(Property Ownership Transfer Agreement)
It's a transfer agreement.

998
00:41:50,666 --> 00:41:52,066
Just as we discussed before,

999
00:41:52,810 --> 00:41:54,506
300,000 compensation per storefront.

1000
00:41:54,787 --> 00:41:55,666
Sign this,

1001
00:41:55,706 --> 00:41:57,747
and you'll get the money within a month.

1002
00:42:04,226 --> 00:42:04,970
A lot of money.

1003
00:42:04,970 --> 00:42:06,442
Hold on.

1004
00:42:08,106 --> 00:42:08,606
Ms. Gao,

1005
00:42:10,267 --> 00:42:11,106
as I know,

1006
00:42:11,347 --> 00:42:13,066
the government
doesn't have that much money.

1007
00:42:13,827 --> 00:42:14,467
So,

1008
00:42:15,186 --> 00:42:16,387
sign this agreement with me.

1009
00:42:17,467 --> 00:42:18,867
I'll give you the money.

1010
00:42:19,226 --> 00:42:19,987
I get the shop,

1011
00:42:20,307 --> 00:42:21,347
and you take the money.

1012
00:42:22,046 --> 00:42:24,066
Your shop will have nothing
to do with you.

1013
00:42:24,706 --> 00:42:26,506
How much would that cost?

1014
00:42:26,730 --> 00:42:27,666
Xuemei,

1015
00:42:28,186 --> 00:42:29,610
you are crazy?

1016
00:42:29,866 --> 00:42:30,698
Should be "Are you".

1017
00:42:32,186 --> 00:42:32,987
It's colloquial.

1018
00:42:34,387 --> 00:42:34,907
Listen,

1019
00:42:36,427 --> 00:42:37,146
I think

1020
00:42:37,907 --> 00:42:38,987
Mr. Zheng and Ms. Li,

1021
00:42:39,186 --> 00:42:41,146
right in front of us all,
staked their careers

1022
00:42:41,267 --> 00:42:42,827
on the fate of the expansion project.

1023
00:42:43,066 --> 00:42:45,827
So, I dare to tie my fate
to Yuehai's future.

1024
00:42:46,427 --> 00:42:47,467
We're all in business.

1025
00:42:47,946 --> 00:42:49,387
We know what matters most.

1026
00:42:49,787 --> 00:42:51,562
Good faith matters most in business.

1027
00:42:52,267 --> 00:42:53,186
I don't know expansion,

1028
00:42:53,747 --> 00:42:55,706
and I don't know if it will succeed.

1029
00:42:56,546 --> 00:42:58,427
But I know Mr. Zheng and Ms. Li

1030
00:42:58,987 --> 00:42:59,506
very well.

1031
00:43:00,706 --> 00:43:01,267
I trust them.

1032
00:43:06,280 --> 00:43:10,990
♪Gently holding your face♪

1033
00:43:13,340 --> 00:43:18,588
♪To dry the tears from your eyes♪

1034
00:43:20,148 --> 00:43:25,341
♪My heart will always be yours♪

1035
00:43:27,156 --> 00:43:32,492
♪Tell me you'll never be alone again♪

1036
00:43:34,120 --> 00:43:38,108
♪Gazing deep into your eyes♪

1037
00:43:41,028 --> 00:43:46,397
♪No further words are needed♪

1038
00:43:48,033 --> 00:43:53,238
♪Tightly holding your hand♪

1039
00:43:54,972 --> 00:44:00,332
♪The warmth has never changed♪

1040
00:44:01,448 --> 00:44:04,556
♪We share the joy♪

1041
00:44:04,884 --> 00:44:08,108
♪We share the pain♪

1042
00:44:08,362 --> 00:44:13,933
♪We hold the same hope deep inside♪

1043
00:44:15,373 --> 00:44:18,372
♪We brave the storm♪

1044
00:44:18,892 --> 00:44:21,884
♪We share the quest♪

1045
00:44:22,325 --> 00:44:28,268
♪We cherish this love we share♪

1046
00:44:31,458 --> 00:44:36,514
♪Whether we've ever met before♪

1047
00:44:38,419 --> 00:44:43,829
♪Be it near or far away♪

1048
00:44:45,420 --> 00:44:50,603
♪My heartfelt wish for you♪

1049
00:44:52,387 --> 00:44:57,517
♪Is for your peace and happiness♪

1050
00:44:58,824 --> 00:45:01,994
♪We share the joy♪

1051
00:45:02,252 --> 00:45:05,320
♪We share the pain♪

1052
00:45:05,744 --> 00:45:11,967
♪We hold the same hope deep inside♪

1053
00:45:12,567 --> 00:45:15,630
♪We brave the storm♪

1054
00:45:15,966 --> 00:45:19,054
♪We share the quest♪

1055
00:45:19,350 --> 00:45:25,527
♪We cherish this love we share♪
